OL,3,CMen's 1991 convictions overturned
OL,4,Cafter 'deliberate police misconduct'
OL,5,Cfound
OL,7,FDespite conceding the misconduct was
OL,8,Findefensible, prosecutors insisted the
OL,9,Fconvictions remained safe because it
OL,10,Fhad no impact on the fairness of the
OL,11,Fcriminal proceedings.
OL,13,FBut two members of the appeal panel,
OL,14,FLord Justice Treacy and Mr Justice
OL,15,FColton, ruled: "The abuse of process
OL,16,Fissues that arise are of such a level
OL,17,Fof deliberate police misconduct to
OL,18,Foffend the court's sense of justice
OL,19,Fand propriety and undermine public
OL,20,Fconfidence in the justice system."
